Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.72,0:00:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I have a hunch that most of
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.00,0:00:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,you probably found yourself in
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.19,0:00:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,this situation before.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.71,0:00:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,A long list of names, a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.36,0:00:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,scrolling, many doubts, until
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.67,0:00:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to embrace the fact
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.69,0:00:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,that you don't know what you're
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.39,0:00:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,doing, so you just wing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.15,0:00:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But is there a better way to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.12,0:00:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,pick fonts?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.99,0:00:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, there is.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.14,0:00:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You're probably familiar with a
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.95,0:00:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,San Francisco font, the system
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.81,0:00:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,font.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.91,0:00:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's minimal, functional, and it
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.90,0:00:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,provides great visual continuity
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.50,0:00:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,between the system and your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.78,0:00:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But sometimes, you need
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.72,0:00:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,something different.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.92,0:00:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps you want your app to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.03,0:00:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,exude sophistication?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.18,0:01:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Or feel literary?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.95,0:01:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Be awkward?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.65,0:01:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Or just loud and upfront?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.30,0:01:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you figure out which type
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.78,0:01:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,facing style is the right one
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.06,0:01:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,for your app?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.62,0:01:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you need to answer at
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.48,0:01:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,least two questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.47,0:01:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What is my intended use?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.09,0:01:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And this will touch on the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.41,0:01:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,functional aspects, "What
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.16,0:01:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,impression do I want to make?"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.72,0:01:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,This requires to look into how
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.11,0:01:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,style affects the visual mood of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.45,0:01:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,an app.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.57,0:01:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Once these questions have
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.58,0:01:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,answers, you can stop thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.13,0:01:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,about the pairing of fonts.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.51,0:01:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But first, I'd like to introduce
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.28,0:01:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,two terms in the context of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.87,0:01:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,typography: Structure and
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.68,0:01:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,contrast.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.95,0:01:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,To better understand typography,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.41,0:01:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,it is usually helpful to look
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.30,0:01:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,into calligraphy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.69,0:01:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Calligraphy is the art of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.66,0:01:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,writing, and to write, you need
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.19,0:01:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,a tool.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.48,0:01:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance, here are three
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.62,0:01:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,commonly used tools around the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.59,0:01:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,world.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.06,0:01:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,On the left, we have the brush,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.15,0:01:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,which is essential to most East
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.62,0:01:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Asian calligraphy and
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.61,0:01:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,typography.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.31,0:01:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,In the middle, we have the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.53,0:02:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Rodney pen or Kalamos.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.74,0:02:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It has defined Roman letter
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.04,0:02:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,forms, the Arabic Naskh style,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.25,0:02:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,or many index scripts.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.32,0:02:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And on the right, we have the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.61,0:02:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,pointed pen, the tool that gives
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.28,0:02:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,precise control of a stroke
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.61,0:02:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,modulation, a feature that
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.28,0:02:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,really shines with some Cyrillic
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.34,0:02:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,glyphs, for instance.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.41,0:02:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But whatever the effect a
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.00,0:02:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,calligraphic tool has, it can
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.88,0:02:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,always be described in terms of
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.42,0:02:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,structure and contrast.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.75,0:02:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And here's structure.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.42,0:02:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You can think of it as the path
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.89,0:02:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,a tool follows to achieve a
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.23,0:02:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,particular shape.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.71,0:02:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Those of us who like to be
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.53,0:02:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,fancy, also use the Latin word
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.22,0:02:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,ductus to refer to structure.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.12,0:02:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, to demonstrate contrast,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.00,0:02:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,let me use a personal favorite
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.37,0:02:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,among the tools I just showed,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.43,0:02:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the pointed pen.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.43,0:02:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,If I drag it across the screen,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.12,0:02:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I get a very simple line.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.49,0:02:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if I do the same but this
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.01,0:02:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,time, pressing as I drag it, I
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.72,0:02:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,introduce weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.67,0:02:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And this modulation of the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.68,0:02:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,stroke is what we call
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.92,0:02:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,"contrast."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.52,0:02:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's now apply this to
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.60,0:03:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,letter forms.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.67,0:03:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Here are two structures for
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.99,0:03:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,lowercase N, or two ducti for
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.82,0:03:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,fancy people.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.65,0:03:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The one on the left, can be
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.52,0:03:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,traced with a single stroke.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.48,0:03:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,This kind of structure is called
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.60,0:03:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,cursive, and is inherently
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.08,0:03:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,dynamic.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.15,0:03:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The one on the right, requires
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.64,0:03:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,several constructed pen strokes,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.32,0:03:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore feels more static.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.20,0:03:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,These monolinear designs have no
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.46,0:03:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,contrast right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.64,0:03:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let me add some.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.87,0:03:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,As we add weight to the vertical
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.64,0:03:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,strokes, the difference between
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.02,0:03:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,thick and thin increases, until
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.23,0:03:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,we reach high contrast.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.79,0:03:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,If I now add weight to the thin
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.20,0:03:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,strokes, we move toward low
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.16,0:03:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,contrast.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.25,0:03:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the main difference with our
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.35,0:03:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,starting point is mostly weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.30,0:03:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you may be thinking now,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.33,0:03:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,"Well, this is all fine and
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.32,0:03:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,dandy, but why do I need to care
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.60,0:03:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,about this?"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.39,0:03:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's have a look at those
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.55,0:03:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,two sentences.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.80,0:03:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,At this particular size, the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.32,0:03:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,bottom line is much easier to
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.64,0:03:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,read than the top line.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.87,0:04:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And we can easily understand why
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.26,0:04:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,if we look closer at each
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.47,0:04:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,design.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.29,0:04:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,On top, we have Big Caslon.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.96,0:04:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And below, Adobe Caslon prompt.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.52,0:04:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Both designs are revivals of the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.14,0:04:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,work of British type founder
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.46,0:04:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,William Caslon, but one is
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.47,0:04:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,designed for this play, and the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.82,0:04:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,other one for text.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.07,0:04:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Now what does this mean,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.95,0:04:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,exactly?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.49,0:04:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The thin strokes in Big Caslon,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.01,0:04:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,produce high contrast, which is
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.39,0:04:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,an appealing graphical feature.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.00,0:04:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks sharp.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.71,0:04:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you scale it down, the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.97,0:04:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,thin strokes will eventually
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.20,0:04:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,disappear and will make reading
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.52,0:04:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,quite unpleasant, if not
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.55,0:04:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.32,0:04:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, Adobe Caslon
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.46,0:04:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Pro has lower contrast and can
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.30,0:04:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,be used as smaller point sizes,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.69,0:04:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,because of its sturdier design.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.22,0:04:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And now the key difference
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.20,0:04:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,between those two designs is
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.66,0:04:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,spacing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.13,0:04:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,For optical reasons, reading
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.78,0:04:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,stays comfortable if the space
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.51,0:04:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,between letters increases as the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.65,0:04:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,point size decreases.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.70,0:04:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Adobe Caslon Pro has looser
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.82,0:05:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,spacing and this contributes to
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.52,0:05:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,a nicer reading experience at
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.08,0:05:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,smaller size.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.08,0:05:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Display and text are really just
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.51,0:05:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,loose terms describing usage.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.35,0:05:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,This play type is meant to draw
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.77,0:05:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.14,0:05:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you typically use it at
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.35,0:05:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,bigger point sizes, which in
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.46,0:05:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,turn allows you to use styles
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.64,0:05:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,with more high -- with higher
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.18,0:05:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,contrast and more elaborate
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.66,0:05:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,details.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.56,0:05:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Text type is about making the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.76,0:05:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,reading experience comfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.15,0:05:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,When picking a text font, you'll
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.10,0:05:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,want to make sure the contrast
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.49,0:05:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,of the type face is such that it
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.25,0:05:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,will scale down nicely.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.27,0:05:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The spacing should also feel
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.41,0:05:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,comfortable at small size.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.41,0:05:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And in general, try avoiding
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.95,0:05:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,extremes of weight or style.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.84,0:05:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,A good reading experience is
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.01,0:05:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,usually the one you don't
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.79,0:05:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.66,0:05:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,For display, you have more
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.25,0:05:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.41,0:05:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the right place to use
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.41,0:05:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the more extreme weights or
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.94,0:05:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,decorative styles.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.45,0:05:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Even in display though, stay
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.92,0:05:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,aware of spacing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.59,0:05:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,A headline usually looks better
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.96,0:05:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,if it's tightly spaced.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.50,0:06:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, now let's talk about
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.69,0:06:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,what everyone is really
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.49,0:06:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,interested in, style.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.79,0:06:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Becoming better at selecting
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.95,0:06:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,fonts as with most things,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.43,0:06:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,requires practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.71,0:06:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a lot of stuff to learn
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.90,0:06:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's perfectly normal to
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.02,0:06:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,feel overwhelmed at first.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.04,0:06:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But there's really only one way
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.34,0:06:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.02,0:06:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to learn how style
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.36,0:06:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,produces an impression.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.30,0:06:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember that app I called
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.28,0:06:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,sophisticated in my intro?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.01,0:06:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I picked that term but
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.71,0:06:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,it's by no means a universal
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.13,0:06:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,qualification.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.69,0:06:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What style conveys is strongly
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.33,0:06:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,tied to subjectivity, and will
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.76,0:06:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,vary from one person to another.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.95,0:06:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,There is one thing you can learn
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.08,0:06:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,about though, and that is what
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.75,0:06:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,people come to associate with a
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.48,0:06:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,given style.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.40,0:06:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, their
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.55,0:06:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,expectations.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.16,0:06:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's look at the type face
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.31,0:06:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,used for the name of the app,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.52,0:06:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Cochin.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.95,0:06:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The style itself is called
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.48,0:06:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,transitional old style.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.51,0:06:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of you probably never heard
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.60,0:06:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,of it, but you've likely been
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.10,0:06:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,exposed to it in books and/or
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.63,0:06:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,magazines.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.21,0:06:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Cochin has very small, lowercase
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.07,0:06:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,letters compared to the upper
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.12,0:06:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,case.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.71,0:06:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,This gives a classic appearance,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.95,0:07:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,which will feel elegant to a lot
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.48,0:07:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.84,0:07:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But these proportions also
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.05,0:07:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,happen to be exaggerated, and
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.62,0:07:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that makes it feel a bit
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.47,0:07:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,whimsical.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.53,0:07:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The companion to Cochin, Snell
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.10,0:07:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Roundhand, is a design mimicking
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.62,0:07:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,calligraphy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.12,0:07:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And you don't have to be a
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.02,0:07:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,calligrapher to get a sense of
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.26,0:07:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,how much skill this calligraphic
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.74,0:07:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,style demands.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.47,0:07:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's elaborate structure and
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.52,0:07:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,high contrast, lends some
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.81,0:07:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,preciousness to this design.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.86,0:07:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if I round them up, I have
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.11,0:07:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,elegant, whimsical, elaborate,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.15,0:07:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and precious.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.11,0:07:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,How's that for sophistication?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.96,0:07:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So, why now would this feel
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.08,0:07:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,literary?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.68,0:07:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The two typefaces we're looking
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.02,0:07:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,at right now, although there is
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.45,0:07:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,a display, and a textile, both
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.34,0:07:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,have typical features of a
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.65,0:07:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,classical book face.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.24,0:07:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why we feel inclined to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.41,0:07:44.83,Default,,0,0,0,,look at this choice as literary.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.54,0:07:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,But that kind of association is
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.92,0:07:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,not natural at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.55,0:07:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It just comes from the fact that
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.70,0:07:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,most of us have been exposed to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.27,0:07:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,those styles in books.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.90,0:07:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,To complete this brief study in
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.36,0:07:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,style, I'd like to look at the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.93,0:07:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,fame and crazed geometric
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.20,0:07:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,sans-serif.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.54,0:08:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a great example of how
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.95,0:08:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the feel of a typographic style
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.46,0:08:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,comes both from form and usage.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.07,0:08:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The first appeal of that style
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.33,0:08:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,is probably -- it's very simple,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.86,0:08:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,geometry, and I'll venture into
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.76,0:08:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,saying that we've seen renewed
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.13,0:08:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,interest recently in that style
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.86,0:08:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,because of our current design
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.97,0:08:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,infatuation with simplicity.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.08,0:08:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But because this style is all
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.70,0:08:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,over the place right now, you
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.75,0:08:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,may be inclined to think that it
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.98,0:08:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,feels very contemporary and
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.26,0:08:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,fresh.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.56,0:08:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But the nerd in me disagrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.29,0:08:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,This style is almost 100 years
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.68,0:08:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,old.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.99,0:08:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And don't get me wrong, I love
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.32,0:08:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,old stuff, but I just won't call
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.24,0:08:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,it fresh.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.77,0:08:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's the beauty of style.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.36,0:08:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It has many layers, and new
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.28,0:08:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,layers of meaning get added
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.39,0:08:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,constantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.87,0:08:41.20,Default,,0,0,0,,To become better at picking font
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.20,0:08:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,styles, you need to become aware
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.87,0:08:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,of those layers, old and new.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.34,0:08:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So, with our growing knowledge
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.55,0:08:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,of typographic style, let's look
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.10,0:08:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,at a few strategies to pair
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.41,0:08:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,fonts.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.37,0:08:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Note the use of the verb "pair"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.82,0:08:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.28,0:08:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no rule against using
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.75,0:08:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,more than two typefaces, but
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.42,0:08:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,trust me, you're better off
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.36,0:09:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,starting small.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.59,0:09:02.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You can always add style later
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.17,0:09:03.29,Default,,0,0,0,,on if you really need them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.85,0:09:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The first point I'd like to make
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.02,0:09:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,here, is about the impact of
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.49,0:09:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,proportions when pairing fonts.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.25,0:09:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's imagine for a moment, you
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.49,0:09:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,have to design an app for WWSC,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.95,0:09:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the Worldwide Sign Painters
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.53,0:09:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Conference.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.17,0:09:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You start off nice and easy with
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.32,0:09:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,this system font, but we're
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.19,0:09:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,missing that sign paintery-vibe.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.37,0:09:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we go back to the font menu
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.08,0:09:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and I kid you not, there's a
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.96,0:09:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,sign painter typeface in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.46,0:09:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds like a perfect match,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.50,0:09:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.63,0:09:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I should mention that us
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.65,0:09:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,type nerds have a term for that
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.82,0:09:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.38,0:09:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,When someone picks a typeface by
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.98,0:09:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,its name, we call that an LTypI,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.01,0:09:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,or Lack of Typographic
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.66,0:09:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.81,0:09:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing wrong with it,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.52,0:09:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,but picking feature out just
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.67,0:09:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,because your app is about the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.59,0:09:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,future might be too much of a
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.86,0:09:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,shortcut.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.17,0:09:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you're going to pick it,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.80,0:09:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,make sure it's because the style
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.25,0:09:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,is appropriate and it serves its
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.91,0:09:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,functional purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.54,0:10:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,At the end of the day, a
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.98,0:10:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,[inaudible] should really just
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.80,0:10:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,be the cherry on top of the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.99,0:10:03.25,Default,,0,0,0,,cake.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.28,0:10:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So, back to this cherry, I'll
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.13,0:10:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,risk offending a few of my
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.12,0:10:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,peers.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.96,0:10:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You start working on a schedule
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.29,0:10:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,for the event, and you decide to
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.95,0:10:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,use both fonts for typographic
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.08,0:10:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,contrast, SF and sign painter.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.87,0:10:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But something's off.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.49,0:10:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The title's look smaller.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.55,0:10:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And to make them look matched,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.94,0:10:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll have to increase the point
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.22,0:10:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,size on that sign painter style.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.59,0:10:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, where does this difference
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.76,0:10:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.04,0:10:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Type designers draw glyphs
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.60,0:10:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,within the bounds of a virtual
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.78,0:10:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,box called a font body.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.33,0:10:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Inside this box, proportion will
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.71,0:10:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,vary from one design to another.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.66,0:10:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The height of a font's body is
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.65,0:10:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,what is referred to as the point
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.89,0:10:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,size.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.66,0:10:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So, at the same point size, two
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.53,0:10:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,fonts can appear to have
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.78,0:10:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,different scales because of
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.10,0:10:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,their design.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.73,0:10:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me show you how this could
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.04,0:10:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,be relevant.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.76,0:10:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's say you're working on a
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.74,0:10:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,dictionary app.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.26,0:10:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Dictionaries require a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.43,0:10:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,typographic hierarchy, and using
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.26,0:11:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,only the weights and italics of
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.34,0:11:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,a [inaudible] might not be
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.84,0:11:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.89,0:11:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You have those descriptives
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.83,0:11:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,stand out, for instance.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.91,0:11:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we decide to go look for a
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.31,0:11:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,serif typeface to create
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.55,0:11:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,typographic contrast.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.43,0:11:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And to try and avoid to tweak
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.69,0:11:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,point sizes left and right,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.00,0:11:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,let's find a serif typeface that
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.40,0:11:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,has close proportions to the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.74,0:11:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,[inaudible].
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.35,0:11:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,This is easily done by setting
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.84,0:11:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,all candidates side by side.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.12,0:11:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,They're the same point size and
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.43,0:11:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,evaluating their apparent scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.69,0:11:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,There is nothing wrong with
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.82,0:11:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,picking a typeface of smaller or
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.55,0:11:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,greater scale, but just bear in
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.41,0:11:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,mind that you'll have to adjust
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.52,0:11:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,point size if you go with that
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.12,0:11:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,twice.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.06,0:11:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's make our life easier
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.17,0:11:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,here and look for the closest
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.33,0:11:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,match available.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.54,0:11:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And we have a winner.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.16,0:11:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, bringing that back in our
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.17,0:11:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,layout, we introduce typographic
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.10,0:11:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,contrast, and we're done.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.85,0:11:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,No need to tweak point sizes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.10,0:11:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're worried that this
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.89,0:11:47.79,Default,,0,0,0,,approach might limit your
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.79,0:11:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,stylistic options, please don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.02,0:11:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,There are thousands of good
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.12,0:11:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,typefaces out there, and quite a
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.51,0:11:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,few type designers release from
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.81,0:11:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,families, with multiple styles
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.73,0:11:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,of consistent proportions.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.53,0:12:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's now experiment a bit
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.05,0:12:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,with pairing text and display
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.81,0:12:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,styles.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.85,0:12:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's start nice and easy
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.46,0:12:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,again with a [inaudible] in a
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.84,0:12:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,news story layout.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.69,0:12:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,This typographic layout has
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.90,0:12:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,strong stylistic continuity.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.75,0:12:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The only difference between text
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.11,0:12:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and headline, are size and the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.85,0:12:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,use of italics.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.69,0:12:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But we might be after something
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.90,0:12:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,with a bit more of a punch.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.89,0:12:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And the first way to get there,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.73,0:12:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the easiest way to get there, is
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.07,0:12:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,to first leverage weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.19,0:12:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Sticking to a single typeface
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.59,0:12:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and pairing some of its variant,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.90,0:12:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,is a very efficient way to
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.31,0:12:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,achieve design consistency.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.43,0:12:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But since we're here to
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.20,0:12:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,experiment, let's keep on trying
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.80,0:12:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,things.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.13,0:12:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We now change the kind of
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.48,0:12:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,typographic contrast from a
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.12,0:12:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,weight difference to a stylistic
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.77,0:12:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.70,0:12:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,When doing these kind of
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.71,0:12:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,pairings, make sure that the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.11,0:12:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,stylistic difference is strong
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.58,0:12:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,enough to be obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.94,0:12:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we have two typestyles of
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.52,0:12:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,both different structures, and
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.17,0:12:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,stroke contrast, so we're in a
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.06,0:12:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,good place.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.35,0:12:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, it is sometimes good
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.99,0:13:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,enough to have a strong display
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.83,0:13:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,typeface and using the system
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.64,0:13:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,font at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.09,0:13:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You're defining your own style,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.42,0:13:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,but also taking advantage of
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.37,0:13:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,[inaudible] performance as a
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.18,0:13:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,typographic workhorse.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.72,0:13:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,But let's keep on experimenting
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.92,0:13:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.56,0:13:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I'd like to use a serif
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.74,0:13:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,typeface down there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.84,0:13:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We return to an understated and
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.50,0:13:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,calm effect like we had in the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.86,0:13:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,beginning, but with a quite
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.21,0:13:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,different flavor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.70,0:13:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,This will now feel more bookish
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.25,0:13:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the type choice, but
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.55,0:13:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,also because of the subdued
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.78,0:13:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,relationship between display and
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.54,0:13:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,text.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.50,0:13:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Books tend to go from
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.02,0:13:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,[inaudible] typographic contrast
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.19,0:13:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,because they're about long
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.44,0:13:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,reading, and of grabbing your
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.89,0:13:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,attention all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.48,0:13:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, a news layout
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.15,0:13:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,may be more [inaudible] this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.60,0:13:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we're using san serif for
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.24,0:13:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,both display and textiles, but
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.06,0:13:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,their structuring weights are so
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.49,0:13:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,different that we still maintain
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.16,0:13:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,clear and strong typographic
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.62,0:13:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,contrast.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.86,0:13:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The display style grabbed your
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.07,0:13:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,attention, provides context,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.93,0:13:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,this is what you're about to
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.82,0:13:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,read, and makes the layout look
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.70,0:13:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,appealing and then the textile
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.82,0:14:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,will let you read the content
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.17,0:14:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,with ease and without
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.23,0:14:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,disruption.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.90,0:14:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So, as you've now seen, there's
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.98,0:14:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,obviously a lot you can do in
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.52,0:14:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,terms of style pairing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.59,0:14:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've only given you a
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.67,0:14:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,glimpse of the possibilities of
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.04,0:14:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,course.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.12,0:14:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The key element is typographic
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.49,0:14:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,contrast.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.34,0:14:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether I did it through size,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.76,0:14:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,weight, or style.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.85,0:14:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, if you want to become
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.97,0:14:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,better at picking fonts, there
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.36,0:14:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,is really no way around learning
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.81,0:14:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,more about typographic styles,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.52,0:14:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,their histories, and evolving
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.77,0:14:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,trends.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.11,0:14:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,This is how you'll become more
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.24,0:14:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,confident in front of that font
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.51,0:14:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,menu.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.50,0:14:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And don't worry, you won't
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.73,0:14:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,become typographic rock stars
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.90,0:14:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,overnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.95,0:14:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And yes, that's a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.28,0:14:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,But at least you know where to
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.62,0:14:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,start.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.17,0:14:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And I have no doubt that you'll
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.52,0:14:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,soon grow into tremendous
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.67,0:14:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,typographers yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.39,0:14:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
